<worksheet >
    <title>FUN-1 Vector Operations and Applications</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>To earn an M on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete both problems. To earn a P on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete 
        problem 2 and one part of problem 1.</p>
  </introduction>  
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in">
        <introduction><p>Let <m>\vec{u}=\langle 3, -2,1\rangle, \vec{v}=\langle 1,-1,1\rangle,</m> 
            and <m>\vec{w}=\langle 2,0,1\rangle</m></p></introduction>
      <task><statement><p>Find <m>\vec{u}\cdot(\vec{v}\times\vec{w})</m></p></statement></task>
      <task><statement><p>Find the vector in the direction of <m>\vec{u}</m> with length of 
        <m>4\vec{v}</m>.</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in">
      <statement><p>Due to gravity, an object that weighs <m>12N</m> slides down a straight 
        frictionless ramp from the point <m>(0,0,9)</m>ft to the point <m>(0,40,0)</m>ft.  How 
        much work is done by gravity?</p></statement>
    </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>